The paper focuses on deep learning and image analysis, specifically using neural style transfer as a regularization technique. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses various deep learning algorithms and techniques, such as convolutional neural networks and transfer learning, which are commonly associated with the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of data augmentation, which is a common technique in the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on a skin lesion classification case study, which falls under the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
